AST MACROS

def indirect_property () => (*obj)::property
	get$() => $1;


The above would be a clean way to make a macro for short hand syntax to
forward one property to another.

===




So that when the parser finds such patterns, they will be "user grammar" and converted into the user defined transformed code and then parse that once its core language.

Many high level expression utilities could just be built on top of the most elementary ones.

Through the customization users can build their own DSL to make things even more powerful1!